Token.Abstract: This protocol exists ONLY so that, if you absolutely need it, you can perform manual subclass registration via [Subclass registerSubclass]. Note that any calls to registerSubclass must happen after parse has been initialized already. This should only ever be needed in the scenario where you may be dynamically creation new Objective-C classes for parse objects, or you are doing conditional subclass registration (e.g. only register class A if config setting 'foo' is defined, otherwise register B).
